By default a [`QListWidgetItem`][1] is not editable so if you want it to be, you must enable the [`Qt::ItemIsEditable`][2] flag:

```
connect(m_addButton, &amp;QPushButton::clicked, this, [&amp;]()
{
	QListWidgetItem *item = new QListWidgetItem;
    item-&gt;setFlags(item-&gt;flags() | Qt::ItemIsEditable); # enable
    m_list-&gt;addItem(item);
    m_list-&gt;setCurrentItem(item);
    m_list-&gt;editItem(item);
});
``` 


  [1]: https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qlistwidgetitem.html
  [2]: https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qt.html#ItemFlag-enum

